    {
        "content": "<p>do you mean that the left side of the <code>or</code> is true if <code>a = b = c</code> and the right side is true if <code>¬(a = b = c)</code>?</p>",
        "id": 508992483,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1743312482
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can probably try to show that a^2/b + b^2 / c + c^2 / a &lt;= 1 if and only if a = b = c. I guess this is a more accurate lean version than what you demonstrated above?</p>",
